We have a customfield that we update via the soap api's.  This field should not appear on an edit screen in Jira. Unfortunately, Jira appears to require that a field appear on an edit screen to be editable via soap. This is a problem for us because we need this field to ONLY be editable via our external scripts that use soap. In order for our external scripts to work, we had to add a tab to the edit screen the includes only this field and HOPE that users do not modify that field.  This leaves us open to a loss of data integrity.  I would like a way to make a field editable even if it is not on an edit screen.

